    "system_architecture": {
      "contracts_analyzed": [
        "LockManager.sol"
      ],
      "inheritance_hierarchy": "LockManager inherits BaseBlastManager (project-specific; provides configStorage access, reconfigure hook, pause/admin/role modifiers), implements ILockManager, and inherits OpenZeppelin ReentrancyGuard. It imports OZ ERC20 but uses IERC20 interface calls (transfer/transferFrom/allowance).",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/ReentrancyGuard.sol",
        "@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20.sol (imported but not directly used; IERC20 methods invoked on ERC20 addresses)",
        "IConfigStorage (external configuration registry; provides getAddress/getUint and onlyConfigStorage gating)",
        "IAccountManager (external rewards/registration; getPlayer and forceHarvest are called)",
        "IMigrationManager (used as a privileged caller exemption during lockdrop NFT reveal mint accounting)",
        "INFTOverlord (external NFT reveal tracking; addReveal called)",
        "ISnuggeryManager (loaded but not used in this file; may be used via inherited BaseBlastManager patterns or future use)"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "None observed in this contract (no Initializable/UUPS/Proxy/Diamond patterns present in shown code). However, dependency addresses are updatable via configStorage->configUpdated(), enabling mutable system wiring without a proxy.",
      "access_control_structure": "Access is enforced via inherited modifiers from BaseBlastManager/BaseConfigStorage (not shown): onlyAdmin (admin governance), onlyConfigStorage (authorized config updater), onlyOneOfRoles([...]) (role-based multisig set of five price feed operators), and notPaused (pausability gate). ReentrancyGuard protects lock/lockOnBehalf/unlock."
    },
